	(407, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.tv/2013/10/31/panel-discussion-running-a-wordpress-development-business/\' title=\'    \'>WordPress.tv: Panel Discussion: Running A WordPress Development Business</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.tv/2013/10/31/ross-jones-the-best-seo-plugin-for-wordpress/\' title=\'    \'>WordPress.tv: Ross Jones: The Best SEO Plugin For WordPress</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.tv/2013/10/30/todd-oneill-whats-content-strategy-and-why-should-i-care/\' title=\'    \'>WordPress.tv: Todd O’Neill: What’s Content Strategy and Why Should I Care?</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/eplmPDEcBQc/huge-collection-of-wordpress-site-logos\' title=\'WPTavern was founded in 2008 and since that time, we’ve published close to 1,500 articles discussing all things WordPress. I’ve made it a habit to use the logo of any site I link to, as the first image presented in the article. After five years, the WPTavern media library is filled with WordPress centric images captured mostly with SnagIt, my favorite screen capturing software. I thought it would be fun if I put together a gallery showing all of the WordPress logo images housed within the Tavern media library. There are around 265 images in this slide show. The images are arranged newest to oldest. As you browse through them, you’re going back in time.  Click to view slideshow. \'>WPTavern: Huge Collection Of WordPress Site Logos</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/x-7qxTGpS4g/the-darkside-of-wordpress\' title=\'WPLift.com has published a cool post that looks into the dark economy surrounding WordPress. That is, those who use WordPress in nefarious ways for profit. Examples include spammers, those who buy automated blog comments, hackers, and the unethical practice of reselling GPL products using trademarks and branding. \'>WPTavern: The Darkside Of WordPress</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
